        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-09-14T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-09-14T06:00:00-05:00" n="272"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                <head>272. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Syria</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d272fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 120.1480/9–1455. Confidential. Received at 8:48 a.m. Repeated to
                        Cairo, Amman, Beirut, Tel Aviv, London, Baghdad, and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-09-14T13:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1955—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>240. From <persName corresp="#p_JE1">Johnston</persName>.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d272fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_JE1">Johnston</persName> arrived in Damascus on
                        September 13.</note> In hour’s conversation with President Quwwatli today I
                    had opportunity explain Jordan Valley Program and seek his estimate of when
                    Foreign Ministers’ meeting might be held. He showed sympathetic interest and
                    indicated new government<note n="3" xml:id="d272fn3">Said al-Ghazzi formed a new
                        government on September 13.</note> would consider as early order of
                    business. He mentioned need Syria act in concert Arab States in view
                    international character program. In course discussion of Lebanese situation<note
                        n="4" xml:id="d272fn4">On September 13, Lebanese Prime Minister Sami Solh
                        resigned after four members of his Cabinet submitted resignations in the
                        course of a parliamentary attack on the Prime Minister. President <persName
                            corresp="#p_CC1">Chamoun</persName> asked <persName corresp="#p_KR1"
                            >Rashid Karame</persName>, Minister of Economy in the outgoing
                        government, to form a new Cabinet.</note> and developments information new
                    government here, he concurred that meeting Foreign Ministers at Cairo might be
                    possible about September 24.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJSJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Moose</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
